cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the approximation of kernel functions using random features and the use of Optical Processing Units (OPUs) for fast and energy-efficient computation. This is a topic that is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), neural networks (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). Given that the paper focuses on applications of kernel ridge regression and transfer learning for image classification, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. However, the use of OPUs for large-scale computation also suggests relevance to cs.DS, cs.NE, and cs.SY.
